de Jean Wyclif,&rdquo; <em>Vivarium</em>, 43(1): 124&ndash;55.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2007, &ldquo;Intentionality and
Truth-Making: Augustine&rsquo;s Influence on Burley and Wyclif&rsquo;s
Propositional Semantics&rdquo;, <em>Vivarium</em>, 45:
283&ndash;97.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2007, <em>Le r&eacute;alisme
propositionnel: S&eacute;mantique et ontologie des propositions chez
Jean Duns Scot, Gauthier Burley, Richard Brinkley et Jean Wyclif</em>,
Paris: Vrin.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2011, &ldquo;Wyclif on the Felicity
(Conditions) of Marriage,&rdquo; <em>Vivarium</em>, 49:
258&ndash;74.</li>

<li>Conti, A.D., 1989, &ldquo;Essenza ed essere nel pensiero della
tarda scolastica (Burley, Wyclif, Paolo Veneto),&rdquo;
<em>Medioevo</em>, 15: 235&ndash;67.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1993, &ldquo;Logica intensionale e
metafisica dell&rsquo;essenza in John Wyclif,&rdquo; <em>Bullettino
dell&rsquo;Istituto Storico Italiano per il Medioevo e Archivio
muratoriano</em>, 99(1): 159&ndash;219.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1997, &ldquo;Analogy and Formal
Distinction: On the Logical Basis of Wyclif&rsquo;s
Metaphysics,&rdquo; <em>Medieval Philosophy and Theology</em>, 6(2):
133&ndash;65.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2006, &ldquo;Wyclif&rsquo;s Logic and
Metaphysics,&rdquo; in Levy, I. C. ed., <em>A Companion to Johm
Wyclif, Late Medieval Theologian</em>, Leiden: Brill.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2008, &ldquo;Categories and Universals in
the Later Middle Ages&rdquo;, in Newton. L.A., <em>Medieval
Commentaries on Aristotle&rsquo;s Categories</em>, Leiden: Brill, pp.
369&ndash;409.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2013, &ldquo;Semantic and Ontological
Aspects of Wyclif&rsquo;s Theory of Supposition,&rdquo;
<em>Vivarium</em>, 51: 304&ndash;26.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2016, &ldquo;Wyclif as an Opponent of
Ockham: a Case of Realist Reaction to Ockham&rsquo;s Approach to
Logic, Metaphysics, and Theology&rdquo;, in Christian Rode ed., <em>A
Companion to Responses to Ockham</em>, Leiden-Boston: Brill, pp.
109&ndash;39.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2023, &ldquo;Wyclif and Paul of Venice on
the Liar Paradox: a Comparison&rdquo;, in S. Read and B. Bartocci
(eds.), <em>Theories of Paradox in the Middle Ages</em>,
Rickmansworth: College Publications, pp. 187&ndash;202.</li>

<li>Dahmus, Joseph, 1952, <em>The Prosecution of John Wyclyf</em>, New
Haven: Yale University Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1960, &ldquo;John Wyclif and the English
Government,&rdquo; <em>Speculum</em>, 35: 51&ndash;60.</li>

<li>Daly, L. J., 1962, <em>The Political Theory of John Wyclif</em>,
Chicago: Loyola University Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1973, &ldquo;Wyclif&rsquo;s Political
Theory: A Century of Study,&rdquo; <em>Medievalia et Humanistica</em>,
4: 177&ndash;87.</li>

<li>Dawson, James Doyne, 1983, &ldquo;Richard Fitzralph and the
Fourteenth Century Poverty Controversies,&rdquo; <em>Journal of
Ecclesiastical History</em>, 34(3): 315&ndash;44.</li>

<li>de Libera, A., 1996, <em>La querelle des universaux: De Platon
&agrave; la fin du Moyen Age</em>, Paris: &Eacute;ditions du Seuil,
pp. 403&ndash;28.</li>

<li>Dipple, Geoffrey, 1994, &ldquo;Uthred and the Friars: Apostolic
Poverty and Clerical Dominion Between Fitzralph and Wyclif,&rdquo;
<em>Traditio</em>, 49: 235&ndash;58.</li>

<li>Doyle, Eric, O.F.M., 1973, &ldquo;William Woodford&rsquo;s <em>De
Dominio Civili Clericorum</em> against John Wyclif,&rdquo;
<em>Archivum Franciscanum Historicum</em>, 66: 49&ndash;109.</li>

<li>Evans, Gillian R., 2006, <em>John Wyclif: Myth and Reality</em>,
London: IVP Academic.</li>

<li>Farr, W., 1974, <em>John Wyclif as Legal Reformer</em>, Leiden: E.
J. Brill.</li>

<li>Fumagalli Beonio Brocchieri, M.-T. &amp; S. Simonetta (eds.),
2003, <em>Wyclif: logica, teologia, politica</em>, Firenze: sismel
&ndash; Edizioni del Galluzzo.</li>

<li>Gaskin, R., 2009, &ldquo;John Wyclif and the Theory of Complexly
Signifiables&rdquo;, <em>Vivarium</em>, 47: 74&ndash;96.</li>

<li>Gellrich, J., 1995, <em>Discourse and Dominion in the Fourteenth
Century</em>; <em>Oral Contexts of Writing in Philosophy, Politics,
and Poetry</em>, Princeton: Princeton University Press.</li>

<li>Ghosh, K., 2002, <em>The Wycliffite Heresy</em>, Cambridge:
Cambridge University Press.</li>

<li>Gilbert, N. W., 1974, &ldquo;Ockham, Wyclif and the <em>via
moderna</em>,&rdquo; in A. Zimmermann, ed., <em>Antiqui und Moderni:
Traditionsbewu&szlig;tsein und Fortschrittsbewu&szlig;tsein im
sp&auml;ten Mittelalter</em>, Berlin: Miscellanea Mediaevalia, pp.
85&ndash;125.</li>

<li>Hoenen, M. J. F. M., 2002, &ldquo;Jean Wyclif et les
<em>universalia realia</em>: le d&eacute;bat sur la notion de
<em>virtus sermonis</em> au Moyen &Acirc;ge tardif et les rapports
entre la th&eacute;ologie et la philosophie,&rdquo; in J.-L.
Sol&egrave;re &amp; Z. Kaluza (eds.), <em>La servante et la
consolatrice. La philosophie dans ses rapports avec la
th&eacute;ologie au Moyen &Acirc;ge</em>, Paris: Vrin, pp.
173&ndash;92.</li>

<li>Hornbeck, J.Patrick, 2010, <em>What is a Lollard? Dissent and
Belief in Late Medieval England</em>, Oxford: Clarendon Press.</li>

<li>Hudson, A., 1988, <em>The Premature Reformation: Wycliffite Texts
and Lollard History</em>, Oxford: Clarendon Press.</li>

<li>Hudson, A. and M. Wilks (eds.), 1987, <em>From Ockham to
Wyclif</em>, Oxford: Blackwell, pp. 165&ndash;77, 185&ndash;215, and
217&ndash;32.</li>

<li>Kaminsky, H., 1963, &ldquo;Wycliffism as Ideology of
Revolution,&rdquo; <em>Church History</em>, 32: 57&ndash;74.</li>

<li>Kenny, A., 1985, <em>Wyclif</em>, Oxford: Clarendon Press.</li>

<li>Kenny, A. (ed.), 1986, <em>Wyclif in his Times</em>, Oxford:
Clarendon Press.</li>

<li>Lahey, S.E., 1997, &ldquo;Wyclif and Rights,&rdquo; <em>Journal of
the History of Ideas</em>, 58: 1&ndash;20.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2003, <em>Philosophy and Politics in the
Thought of John Wyclif</em>, Cambridge: Cambridge University
Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2009, <em>John Wyclif</em>, Oxford: Oxford
University Press.</li>

<li>Leff, G., 1967, <em>Heresy in the Later Middel Ages</em>, 2 vols.,
Manchester: Manchester University Press, Volume 2, pp.
494&ndash;573.</li>

<li>Levy, I. C., 2003, <em>Scriptural Logic, Rea Presence, and the
Parameters of Orthodoxy</em>, Milwaukee: Marquette University
Press.</li>

<li>Levy, I. C. (ed.), 2006, <em>A Companion to Johm Wyclif, Late
Medieval Theologian</em>, Leiden: Brill.</li>

<li>McFarlane, K. B., 1952, <em>John Wycliffe and the Beginnings of
English Non-Conformity</em>, London: English Universities Press.</li>

<li>Michael, E., 2003, &ldquo;John Wyclif on Body and Mind,&rdquo;
<em>Journal of the History of Ideas</em>, 64: 343&ndash;60.</li>

<li>Read, S., 1985, &ldquo;<em>I promise a penny that I do not
promise</em>. The Realist/Nominalist Debate over Intensional
Propositions in Fourteenth-Century British Logic and its Contemporary
Relevance,&rdquo; in P.O. Lewry (ed.), <em>The Rise of British
Logic</em>, Toronto: Pontifical Institute of Medieval Studies, pp.
335&ndash;59.</li>

<li>Robson, J. A., 1961, <em>Wyclif and the Oxford Schools</em>,
Cambridge: Cambridge University Press.</li>

<li>Shogimen, Takashi, 2006, &ldquo;Wyclif&rsquo;s Ecclesiology and
Political Thought,&rdquo; in <em>A Companion to John Wyclif</em>, Ian
C. Levy (ed.), Leiden: Brill, pp. 199&ndash;240.</li>

<li>Simonetta, S., 1995, &ldquo;John Wyclif between Utopia and
Plan,&rdquo; in <em>Soci&eacute;t&eacute; et &Eacute;glise: Textes et
discussions dans les universit&eacute;s de l&rsquo;Europe centrale
pendant le moyen &acirc;ge tardif</em>, Turnhout: Brepols, pp.
65&ndash;86.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1996, &ldquo;La maturazione del progetto
riformatore di Giovanni Wyclif: dal <em>De civili dominio</em> al
<em>De officio regis</em>,&rdquo; <em>Medioevo</em>, 22:
225&ndash;58.</li>

<li>Spade, P. V., 1985, &ldquo;Introduction,&rdquo; in J. Wyclif,
<em>On Universals</em>, A. Kenny (trans.), Oxford: Clarendon, pp.
vii-l.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2005, &ldquo;The Problem of Universals and
Wyclif&rsquo;s Alleged &lsquo;Ultrarealism&rsquo;,&rdquo;
<em>Vivarium</em>, 43(1): 111&ndash;23.</li>

<li>Spade, P. V. &amp; G. A. Wilson, 1986, &ldquo;Introduction,&rdquo;
in J. Wyclif, <em>Summa insolubilium</em>, P. V. Spade &amp; G. A.
Wilson, ed., Binghamton, N.Y.: Medieval and Renaissance Texts and
Studies.</li>

<li>Spruyt, J., 2008, &ldquo;The Unity of Semantics and Ontology.
Wyclif&rsquo;s Treatment of the <em>fallacia accidentis</em>&rdquo;,
<em>Vivarium</em>, 46(1): 24&ndash;58.</li>

<li>Tatnall, Edith C., 1969, &ldquo;John Wyclif and Ecclesia
Anglicana,&rdquo; <em>Journal of Theological History</em>, 20:
19&ndash;43.</li>

<li>Thomson, S. H., 1931, &ldquo;The Philosophical Basis of
Wyclif&rsquo;s Theology,&rdquo; <em>Journal of Religion</em>, 11:
86&ndash;116.</li>

<li>Thomson, W. R., 1983, <em>The Latin Writings of John Wyclif: An
Annotated Catalog</em>, Toronto: Pontfical Institute of Mediaeval
Studies.</li>

<li>Walsh, K. &amp; D. Wood (eds.), 1985, <em>The Bible in the
Medieval World</em>, Oxford: Blackwell, pp. 269&ndash;315.</li>

<li>Wilks, M., 1965, &ldquo;Predestination, Property and Power:
Wyclif&rsquo;s Theory of Dominion and Grace,&rdquo; <em>Studies in
Church History</em>, 2: 220&ndash;36.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1972, &ldquo;<em>Reformatio regni</em>:
Wyclif and Hus: Leaders of Religious Protest Movements,&rdquo;
<em>Studies in Church History</em>, 9: 109&ndash;30.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2000, <em>Wyclif: Political Ideas and
Practice</em>, Anne Hudson (ed.), Oxford: Oxbow Books.</li>

<li>Workman, H. B., 1926, <em>John Wyclif: A Study of the English
Medieval Church</em>, 2 volumes, Oxford: Clarendon Press.</li>

<li>Zuckerman, Charles, 1975, &ldquo;The Relationship of Theories of
Universals to Theories of Church Government in the Middle Ages: A
Critique of Previous Views,&rdquo; <em>Journal of the History of
Ideas</em>, 35: 575&ndash;94.</li>
</ul>
